    <intro>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;" face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;What do you think this statement by Barr and Tagg (1995) means? &lt;i&gt;“When we focus on instruction rather than learning, we confuse the means with the ends.”&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;" face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Do you agree or disagree with this statement? What are the reasons for your agreement or disagreement?    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;How can we do more facilitation of discovery learning and less dispensing of knowledge? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;&lt;span face="Calibri"&gt;Click below on "Add a new discussion topic"  to respond to these questions and share strategies that you have found to be effective.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;span size="3" face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;" size="3"&gt;-----&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;" size="3"&gt;Source: Barr, R. B. &amp;amp; Tagg, J. (1995, November/December). From teaching to learning--a new paradigm for undergraduate education. &lt;i&gt;Change Magazine&lt;/i&gt;, 27 (6): 12-25.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</intro>
